---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ScrollReveal from '../components/ScrollReveal.astro';
import Accordion from '../components/Accordion.astro';
import ComparisonBar from '../components/ComparisonBar.astro';
import TrustCertificate from '../components/TrustCertificate.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About | Tom Pickup"
  description="About Tom Pickup, Lancashire County Councillor for Padiham and Burnley West. Lead Member for Finance and Resources. Parish Councillor, Stocks Massey Chairman. Reform UK."
>
  <!-- Section 1: Page Header + Bio -->
  <section class="page-header-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="bio-grid">
        <div class="bio-photo-wrap">
          <div class="bio-photo-glow"></div>
          <div class="bio-photo">
            <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Tom Pickup, Lancashire County Councillor for Padiham and Burnley West" loading="eager" />
          </div>
          <div class="bio-badges">
            <span class="bio-badge bio-badge-accent">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"></path><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"></polyline></svg>
              Elected May 2025
            </span>
            <span class="bio-badge bio-badge-reform">Reform UK</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bio-text">
          <h1>Tom <span class="gradient-text">Pickup</span></h1>
          <p class="bio-role">Lancashire County Councillor for <strong>Padiham &amp; Burnley West</strong></p>

          <div class="bio-roles">
            <div class="bio-role-chip">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M16 21V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2h-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16"></path></svg>
              Lead Member for Finance &amp; Resources
            </div>
            <div class="bio-role-chip">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"></path><polyline points="9 22 9 12 15 12 15 22"></polyline></svg>
              Parish Councillor &middot; Clowbridge with Dunnockshaw
            </div>
            <div class="bio-role-chip">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20.84 4.61a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 0L12 5.67l-1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0-7.78 7.78l1.06 1.06L12 21.23l7.78-7.78 1.06-1.06a5.5 5.5 0 0 0 0-7.78z"></path></svg>
              Chairman &middot; Stocks Massey Bequest Fund
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bio-body">
            <p>
              I grew up in this area and I care deeply about its future. Like many residents, I watched
              council tax bills climb year after year while potholes multiplied, bins got missed, and the
              answers from County Hall never quite added up. I decided to stop complaining and start doing
              something about it.
            </p>
            <p>
              In May 2025, Lancashire voted for change. Decisively. Reform won 53 of 84 seats,
              the largest majority any party has held at County Hall. As Lead Member for Finance and
              Resources, we inherited a &pound;28 million overspend, &pound;350 million in concealed bond
              losses, and a savings programme that had collapsed from 91% delivery to just 48%.
              We&rsquo;ve turned it around: the lowest council tax rise in 12 years, a balanced
              budget, and all five care homes saved.
            </p>
            <p>
              I was elected on a simple promise: transparency, accountability, and putting residents first.
              I don't do politics-as-usual. I ask the awkward questions, I dig into the numbers, and I
              publish what I find &mdash; because the people paying the bills have a right to know where
              their money goes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Key Stats -->
  <section class="stats-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="stats-grid stagger-children">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" style="color: #30d158;">3.80%</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Lowest CT Rise in 12 Years</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" style="color: #12b6cf;">&pound;28M&rarr;&pound;6M</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Inherited Overspend Corrected</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" style="color: #ff9f0a;">&pound;1.33B</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Budget Oversight</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" style="color: #bf5af2;">&pound;12B</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Pension Fund Committee</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" style="color: #ff453a;">&pound;350M</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Bond Losses Exposed</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" style="color: #30d158;">&pound;18K</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Awarded to Burnley Arts</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: Committee Memberships -->
  <section class="committees-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Committees &amp; Roles</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">The committees I sit on and the roles I hold across Lancashire governance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="committees-grid stagger-children">
          <div class="committee-card committee-card-cabinet">
            <div class="committee-tier">Cabinet</div>
            <h3>Lead Member for Finance &amp; Resources</h3>
            <p>Overseeing Lancashire County Council&rsquo;s &pound;1.33 billion annual budget, financial strategy, treasury management, and council tax setting. Responsible for the council&rsquo;s entire financial operation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="committee-card">
            <div class="committee-tier">Pension Fund</div>
            <h3>Lancashire Pension Fund Committee</h3>
            <p>Oversight of the &pound;12 billion Lancashire Pension Fund, one of the largest local authority pension funds in England, serving 192,000 members.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="committee-card">
            <div class="committee-tier">Combined Authority</div>
            <h3>LCCA Audit &amp; Risk Committee</h3>
            <p>Scrutiny of the Lancashire Combined County Authority&rsquo;s financial controls, risk management, and value-for-money assessments.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="committee-card">
            <div class="committee-tier">Scrutiny</div>
            <h3>Overview &amp; Scrutiny Committee</h3>
            <p>Holding the executive to account through evidence-based inquiry, policy review, and pre-decision scrutiny of major council decisions.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="committee-card">
            <div class="committee-tier">Parish</div>
            <h3>Clowbridge with Dunnockshaw Parish Council</h3>
            <p>Parish councillor for this rural community, dealing with local environmental, planning and community matters in the Rossendale Valley area.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="committee-card">
            <div class="committee-tier">Charity</div>
            <h3>Stocks Massey Bequest Fund</h3>
            <p>Chairman of the Joint Advisory Committee. Distributing grants to arts organisations across Burnley from this registered charity established under the Edward Stocks Massey bequest.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: My Priorities -->
  <section class="priorities-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">My Priorities</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="priorities-grid stagger-children">
          <div class="priority-card card">
            <div class="priority-icon" style="color: var(--accent);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8-11-8-11-8z"></path>
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"></circle>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Radical Transparency</h3>
            <p>
              Open data, public scrutiny, and no backroom deals. Every council decision should be
              visible to the people who pay for it. I publish my findings, share the data, and
              invite challenge.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="priority-card card">
            <div class="priority-icon" style="color: var(--accent-green);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Accountable Governance</h3>
            <p>
              Councillors and officers should answer to residents, not the other way round.
              I challenge complacency, question spending decisions, and hold the executive
              to account in every meeting.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="priority-card card">
            <div class="priority-icon" style="color: var(--accent-orange);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"></polyline>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Data-Driven Decisions</h3>
            <p>
              Gut feeling and party loyalty shouldn't drive council policy. I use real data
              to understand problems, measure performance, and propose solutions. The numbers
              don't lie.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="priority-card card">
            <div class="priority-icon" style="color: var(--accent-purple);">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"></path>
                <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"></circle>
                <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"></path>
                <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Residents First</h3>
            <p>
              Every decision I make starts with one question: is this good for the people of
              Padiham and Burnley West? I'm not here for a career in politics. I'm here to
              serve my community.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Timeline -->
  <section class="timeline-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Key Milestones</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">May 2025</span>
              <h3>Elected to Lancashire County Council</h3>
              <p>
                Won Padiham and Burnley West for Reform UK, joining the largest Reform
                group on any county council in England with 53 of 84 seats.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">May 2025</span>
              <h3>Appointed Lead Member for Finance &amp; Resources</h3>
              <p>
                Appointed to the cabinet, taking charge of the council's &pound;986 million
                net revenue budget and financial strategy.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">Summer 2025</span>
              <h3>Secured Future of Five Care Homes</h3>
              <p>
                Inherited a Conservative consultation on closures. Listened to 1,600+ residents
                and secured their future with new investment pledged.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">Autumn 2025</span>
              <h3>Exposed &pound;350M Bond Losses</h3>
              <p>
                Uncovered that &pound;519M invested in VeLTIP bonds was worth just &pound;169M &mdash;
                losses the previous administration failed to transparently report to councillors.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">February 2026</span>
              <h3>Delivered Reform&rsquo;s First Budget</h3>
              <p>
                Balanced a &pound;1.33 billion budget with the lowest council tax rise in
                12 years (3.80%). Corrected the &pound;28 million inherited overspend without
                cutting front-line services.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-card card">
              <span class="timeline-date">Ongoing</span>
              <h3>Community Engagement</h3>
              <p>
                Holding regular surgeries and being available to residents. Your concerns
                drive my work at County Hall &mdash; from road repairs and planning issues
                to scrutinising budgets.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: Reform at LCC -->
  <section class="reform-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Reform at Lancashire County Council</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="reform-content">
          <p>
            When the Conservatives left County Hall, they left behind a mess: a &pound;28 million
            overspend, savings delivery that had collapsed from 91% to 48%, council tax raised to
            the legal maximum in 7 of 8 years, and &pound;350 million in bond losses they never
            transparently reported.
          </p>
          <p>
            In less than a year, Reform has delivered the lowest council tax rise in 12 years,
            corrected the inherited overspend, saved all five county care homes, and stopped
            councillors collecting salaries for pension fund directorships. We identified &pound;5
            in every &pound;100 of council spending as potential savings. The 2026/27 budget is balanced
            at &pound;1.33 billion, without cutting front-line services.
          </p>

          <div class="reform-comparisons">
            <ComparisonBar
              title="Council Tax Rise"
              reformValue="3.80%"
              reformPercent={63}
              conValue="4.99%"
              conPercent={83}
              lowerIsBetter={true}
              annotation="Reform delivered the lowest council tax rise in 12 years"
            />
            <ComparisonBar
              title="Savings Delivery Rate"
              reformValue="90%+"
              reformPercent={90}
              conValue="48%"
              conPercent={48}
              annotation="Conservative savings delivery collapsed over 8 years"
            />
          </div>

          <p>
            This is what happens when you put people who care about value for money in charge of
            the public purse. Lancashire voted for change, and change is being delivered.
          </p>

          <div class="reform-trust">
            <TrustCertificate />
          </div>

          <div class="reform-links">
            <a href="/lancashire/" class="btn-primary">Full LCC Report</a>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn-secondary">Get in Touch</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 7: Accessibility Statement -->
  <section class="accessibility-section" id="accessibility">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <ScrollReveal>
        <div class="accessibility-card card">
          <h2>Accessibility Statement</h2>
          <p>
            This website aims to be accessible to as many people as possible, in line with
            <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> guidelines. The site is built with semantic HTML,
            supports keyboard navigation, provides sufficient colour contrast, and respects user
            preferences for reduced motion.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you encounter any accessibility issues or have suggestions for improvement,
            please <a href="/contact/">get in touch</a>. I take accessibility seriously and
            will work to resolve any barriers as quickly as possible.
          </p>
        </div>
      </ScrollReveal>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ---- Bio Header Section ---- */
  .page-header-section {
    padding: 7rem 0 var(--space-xl);
  }

  .bio-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2xl);
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Photo */
  .bio-photo-wrap {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    position: relative;
  }

  .bio-photo-glow {
    position: absolute;
    width: 280px;
    height: 280px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(18, 182, 207, 0.2) 0%, transparent 70%);
    filter: blur(40px);
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -55%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .bio-photo {
    position: relative;
    width: 240px;
    height: 240px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 3px solid rgba(18, 182, 207, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(18, 182, 207, 0.15), 0 20px 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  }

  .bio-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .bio-badges {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .bio-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    padding: 5px 14px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .bio-badge-accent {
    background: rgba(48, 209, 88, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(48, 209, 88, 0.2);
    color: #30d158;
  }

  .bio-badge-reform {
    background: rgba(18, 182, 207, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(18, 182, 207, 0.2);
    color: #12b6cf;
  }

  /* Bio text */
  .bio-text h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    color: #fff;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .bio-role {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .bio-role strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .bio-roles {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .bio-role-chip {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 8px 16px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: rgba(28, 28, 30, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .bio-role-chip svg {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .bio-body p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .bio-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Stats Section ---- */
  .stats-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(6, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .stat-card {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-md);
    background: rgba(28, 28, 30, 0.5);
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(1.2);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(1.2);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-normal), transform var(--transition-normal);
  }

  .stat-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .stat-value {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .stat-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  /* ---- Committees ---- */
  .committees-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .committees-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .committee-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: rgba(28, 28, 30, 0.5);
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(1.2);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(16px) saturate(1.2);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    transition: border-color var(--transition-normal), box-shadow var(--transition-normal), transform var(--transition-normal);
  }

  .committee-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .committee-card-cabinet {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .committee-tier {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--accent);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    background: rgba(18, 182, 207, 0.08);
    border-radius: 9999px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .committee-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .committee-card p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Priorities ---- */
  .priorities-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .priorities-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .priority-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .priority-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    transition: transform var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .priority-card:hover .priority-icon {
    transform: scale(1.08) rotate(-3deg);
  }

  .priority-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .priority-card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Timeline ---- */
  .timeline-section {
    padding: 0 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
